HOUSE BILL No. 1065
A BILL FOR AN ACT to amend the Indiana Code concerning
criminal law and procedure.
Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the State of Indiana:
1 SECTION 1. IC 35-31.5-2-146.5 IS ADDED TO THE INDIANA
2 CODE AS A NEW SECTION TO READ AS FOLLOWS
3 [EFFECTIVE JULY 1, 2026]: Sec. 146.5. "Gratuity", for purposes
4 of IC 35-44.1-1-2.5, has the meaning set forth in IC 35-44.1-1-2.5.
5 SECTION 2. IC 35-44.1-1-2.5 IS ADDED TO THE INDIANA
6 CODE AS A NEW SECTION TO READ AS FOLLOWS
7 [EFFECTIVE JULY 1, 2026]: Sec. 2.5. (a) As used in this section,
8 "gratuity" means a payment made to a public servant after an
9 official act as a reward or token of appreciation. However, the
10 term does not include:
11 (1) a good or service that is:
12 (A) subject to a reporting requirement; or
13 (B) otherwise authorized;
14 under a rule or code of ethics that applies to the donor or
15 public servant;
16 (2) a good or service having a de minimis value of less than
17 one hundred dollars ($100);
2026 IN 1065—LS 6334/DI 107

2
1 (3) an item that is primarily ceremonial or commemorative,
2 such as a plaque, trophy, certificate, framed photo, or similar
3 item;
4 (4) a political contribution subject to IC 3-9-2 that is reported
5 in accordance with applicable law; or
6 (5) salary, wages, a bonus, or any other form of work related
7 compensation:
8 (A) from the governmental entity that employs the public
9 servant; and
10 (B) that the public servant is legally authorized to receive.
11 (b) As used in this section, "public servant" includes a former
12 public servant.
13 (c) A person who provides a gratuity to a public servant, with
14 the intent to reward the public servant for an official act
15 performed by the public servant in the public servant's official
16 capacity, commits providing an unlawful gratuity to a public
17 servant, a Class A misdemeanor. However, the offense is a Level 6
18 felony if the fair market value of the gratuity is at least seven
19 hundred fifty dollars ($750).
20 (d) A public servant who:
21 (1) solicits or accepts a gratuity from another person; and
22 (2) either:
23 (A) solicits the gratuity as a reward for; or
24 (B) knows or reasonably should know that the gratuity is
25 offered as a reward for;
26 an official act performed by the public servant in the public
27 servant's official capacity;
28 commits soliciting or accepting an unlawful gratuity, a Class A
29 misdemeanor. However, the offense is a Level 6 felony if the fair
30 market value of the gratuity is at least seven hundred fifty dollars
31 ($750).
